Patch Set 4: I would prefer that you didn't merge this

In the Nova cinder driver we do it like this:

https://github.com/openstack/nova/blob/master/nova/volume/cinder.py#L34

----

Instead of adding individual flags for each part of the service catalog would it be better if we did something similar and added a single (slighly overloaded) config option which controls all of the settings.

Patch Set 4:

That's a great suggestion, Dan. I'd love to see us use that same paradigm here.

Patch Set 4: I would prefer that you didn't merge this

The commit message needs a DocImpact flag, as it adds/modifies a configuration option.

http://wiki.openstack.org/GitCommitMessages?highlight=%28DocImpact%29#Including_external_references
